<DOC><DOCNO> AP880527-0212 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-27-88 2052EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r p AM-BRF--GOP-Meeting     05-27 0186</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--GOP-Meeting,190</SECOND><HEAD>GOP To Hold Unity Meeting In Denver</HEAD><DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Vice President George Bush and hundreds of WesternGOP leaders will meet here next month to show their support of theparty's presidential ticket and Republican candidates for otheroffices.   The event, which will begin June 10, is the first of fourplanned by the Republican National Committee. Other such gatheringswill be in Boston, Chicago and Atlanta later this summer.   Tom Hockaday, the Western regional political director for theBush campaign, said the purpose of the meeting is ``to bringtogether not only the vice president but other (former)presidential aspirants as well as to show we are all workingtogether to elect the vice president.''   However, only one of the five former candidates _ Rep. Jack Kempof New York _ has said he will attend the two-day event.   Spokeswomen for television evangelist Pat Robertson, formerDelaware Gov. Pete DuPont and Alexander Haig all said the formercandidates will not attend because of scheduling conflicts. Sen.Bob Dole of Kansas has not decided whether to attend, a spokeswomanfor Dole said.</TEXT></DOC>